n of purity of blood over time, arguing that the concept's enduring religious, genealogical, and gendered meanings and the archival practices it promoted came to shape the region's patriotic and racial ideologies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362659140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626591423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626591/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles